# v0.1 Home-Linux-Server Build Checklist

## Planning
- [ ] Define purpose of v0.1 (intentionally insecure baseline)
- [ ] Select host environment (VM or bare metal)
- [ ] Select Linux distribution and version
- [ ] Define version naming and documentation rules

## Base Installation
- [ ] Install Linux OS
- [ ] Create primary admin user
- [ ] Set intentionally weak password (documented)
- [ ] Enable SSH with password authentication

## Services (Attack Surface)
- [ ] Install web server (Apache or Nginx)
- [ ] Confirm web service reachable
- [ ] Leave default configurations unchanged
- [ ] Expose at least one sensitive file (intentional)

## Network
- [ ] Use permissive/default firewall rules
- [ ] Confirm SSH (22) open
- [ ] Confirm HTTP (80) open

## Logging (Baseline Only)
- [ ] Confirm system logs exist locally
- [ ] No log forwarding or alerts configured

## Validation
- [ ] Confirm server IP address
- [ ] Confirm services running
- [ ] Document open ports
- [ ] Take screenshots or notes as evidence

## Documentation
- [ ] Update `versions/v0.1-insecure-baseline.md`
- [ ] Document server build details
- [ ] Commit changes to GitHub
